properties.description: The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: repository
properties.description: (Required) The GitHub repository name.

properties.name: branch
properties.description: (Required) The Git branch to protect.

properties.name: enforce_admins
properties.description: (Optional) Boolean, setting this to true enforces status checks for repository administrators.

properties.name: require_signed_commits
properties.description: (Optional) Boolean, setting this to true requires all commits to be signed with GPG.

properties.name: required_status_checks
properties.description: (Optional) Enforce restrictions for required status checks. See Required Status Checks below for details.

properties.name: required_pull_request_reviews
properties.description: (Optional) Enforce restrictions for pull request reviews. See Required Pull Request Reviews below for details.

properties.name: restrictions
properties.description: (Optional) Enforce restrictions for the users and teams that may push to the branch. See Restrictions below for details.

properties.name: required-status-checks
properties.description: » Required Status Checks
required_status_checks supports the following arguments:

properties.name: strict
properties.description: : (Optional) Require branches to be up to date before merging. Defaults to false.

properties.name: contexts
properties.description: : (Optional) The list of status checks to require in order to merge into this branch. No status checks are required by default.

properties.name: required-pull-request-reviews
properties.description: » Required Pull Request Reviews
required_pull_request_reviews supports the following arguments:

properties.name: dismiss_stale_reviews
properties.description: : (Optional) Dismiss approved reviews automatically when a new commit is pushed. Defaults to false.

properties.name: dismissal_users
properties.description: : (Optional) The list of user logins with dismissal access

properties.name: dismissal_teams
properties.description: : (Optional) The list of team slugs with dismissal access. Always use slug of the team, not its name. Each team already has to have access to the repository.

properties.name: require_code_owner_reviews
properties.description: : (Optional) Require an approved review in pull requests including files with a designated code owner. Defaults to false.

properties.name: required_approving_review_count
properties.description: : (Optional) Require x number of approvals to satisfy branch protection requirements. If this is specified it must be a number between 1-6. This requirement matches Github's API, see the upstream documentation for more information.

properties.name: restrictions-1
properties.description: » Restrictions
restrictions supports the following arguments:

properties.name: users
properties.description: : (Optional) The list of user logins with push access.

properties.name: teams
properties.description: : (Optional) The list of team slugs with push access. Always use slug of the team, not its name. Each team already has to have access to the repository.
restrictions is only available for organization-owned repositories.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: repository
properties.description: • repository - (Required) The GitHub repository

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the label.

properties.name: color
properties.description: • color - (Required) A 6 character hex code, without the leading #, identifying the color of the label.

properties.name: description
properties.description: • description - (Optional) A short description of the label.

properties.name: url
properties.description: • url - (Computed) The URL to the issue label
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: username
properties.description: (Required) The user to add to the organization.

properties.name: role
properties.description: (Optional) The role of the user within the organization. Must be one of member or admin. Defaults to member.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: username
properties.description: (Required) The name of the user to block.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the project.

properties.name: body
properties.description: • body - (Optional) The body of the project.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: events
properties.description: • events - (Required) A list of events which should trigger the webhook. See a list of available events

properties.name: configuration
properties.description: • configuration - (Required) key/value pair of configuration for this webhook. Available keys are url, content_type, secret and insecure_ssl.

properties.name: active
properties.description: • active - (Optional) Indicate of the webhook should receive events. Defaults to true.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Optional) The type of the webhook. web is the default and the only option.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: project_id
properties.description: • project_id - (Required) The id of an existing project that the column will be created in.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the column.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the repository.

properties.name: description
properties.description: • description - (Optional) A description of the repository.

properties.name: homepage_url
properties.description: • homepage_url - (Optional) URL of a page describing the project.

properties.name: private
properties.description: • private - (Optional) Set to true to create a private repository. Repositories are created as public (e.g. open source) by default.

properties.name: has_issues
properties.description: • has_issues - (Optional) Set to true to enable the GitHub Issues features on the repository.

properties.name: has_projects
properties.description: • has_projects - (Optional) Set to true to enable the GitHub Projects features on the repository. Per the github documentation when in an organization that has disabled repository projects it will default to false and will otherwise default to true. If you specify true when it has been disabled it will return an error.

properties.name: has_wiki
properties.description: • has_wiki - (Optional) Set to true to enable the GitHub Wiki features on the repository.

properties.name: allow_merge_commit
properties.description: • allow_merge_commit - (Optional) Set to false to disable merge commits on the repository.

properties.name: allow_squash_merge
properties.description: • allow_squash_merge - (Optional) Set to false to disable squash merges on the repository.

properties.name: allow_rebase_merge
properties.description: • allow_rebase_merge - (Optional) Set to false to disable rebase merges on the repository.

properties.name: has_downloads
properties.description: • has_downloads - (Optional) Set to true to enable the (deprecated) downloads features on the repository.

properties.name: auto_init
properties.description: • auto_init - (Optional) Set to true to produce an initial commit in the repository.

properties.name: gitignore_template
properties.description: • gitignore_template - (Optional) Use the name of the template without the extension. For example, "Haskell".

properties.name: license_template
properties.description: • license_template - (Optional) Use the name of the template without the extension. For example, "mit" or "mpl-2.0".

properties.name: default_branch
properties.description: • default_branch - (Optional) The name of the default branch of the repository. NOTE: This can only be set after a repository has already been created, and after a correct reference has been created for the target branch inside the repository. This means a user will have to omit this parameter from the initial repository creation and create the target branch inside of the repository prior to setting this attribute.

properties.name: archived
properties.description: • archived - (Optional) Specifies if the repository should be archived. Defaults to false.

properties.name: topics
properties.description: • topics - (Optional) The list of topics of the repository.
NOTE Currently, the API does not support unarchiving.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: repository
properties.description: (Required) The GitHub repository

properties.name: username
properties.description: (Required) The user to add to the repository as a collaborator.

properties.name: permission
properties.description: (Optional) The permission of the outside collaborator for the repository. Must be one of pull, push, or admin. Defaults to push.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: key
properties.description: (Required) A ssh key.

properties.name: read_only
properties.description: (Required) A boolean qualifying the key to be either read only or read/write.

properties.name: repository
properties.description: (Required) Name of the GitHub repository.

properties.name: title
properties.description: (Required) A title.
Changing any of the fields forces re-creating the resource.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Required) The name of the project.

properties.name: repository
properties.description: • repository - (Required) The repository of the project.

properties.name: body
properties.description: • body - (Optional) The body of the project.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: repository
properties.description: • repository - (Required) The repository of the webhook.

properties.name: events
properties.description: • events - (Required) A list of events which should trigger the webhook. See a list of available events.

properties.name: configuration
properties.description: • configuration - (Required) key/value pair of configuration for this webhook. Available keys are url, content_type, secret and insecure_ssl. secret is the shared secret, see API documentation.

properties.name: active
properties.description: • active - (Optional) Indicate of the webhook should receive events. Defaults to true.

properties.name: name
properties.description: • name - (Optional) The type of the webhook. web is the default and the only option.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: name
properties.description: (Required) The name of the team.

properties.name: description
properties.description: (Optional) A description of the team.

properties.name: privacy
properties.description: (Optional) The level of privacy for the team. Must be one of secret or closed. Defaults to secret.

properties.name: parent_team_id
properties.description: (Optional) The ID of the parent team, if this is a nested team.

properties.name: ldap_dn
properties.description: (Optional) The LDAP Distinguished Name of the group where membership will be synchronized. Only available in GitHub Enterprise.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: team_id
properties.description: (Required) The GitHub team id

properties.name: username
properties.description: (Required) The user to add to the team.

properties.name: role
properties.description: (Optional) The role of the user within the team. Must be one of member or maintainer. Defaults to member.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: team_id
properties.description: (Required) The GitHub team id

properties.name: repository
properties.description: (Required) The repository to add to the team.

properties.name: permission
properties.description: (Optional) The permissions of team members regarding the repository. Must be one of pull, push, or admin. Defaults to pull.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: armored_public_key
properties.description: (Required) Your public GPG key, generated in ASCII-armored format. See Generating a new GPG key for help on creating a GPG key.
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: invitation_id
properties.description: (Required) ID of the invitation to accept
The following arguments are supported:

properties.name: title
properties.description: (Required) A descriptive name for the new key. e.g. Personal MacBook Air

properties.name: key
properties.description: (Required) The public SSH key to add to your GitHub account.
